  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I'd suggest not going with RSA, and instead go with ed25519. One reason is efficiency. The other reason is that ed25519 pubkeys are much smaller and can be inlined in the peer ID. Using RSA creates a level of indirection where the peer ID contains the hash of the pubkey. This is generally awkward work with, and especially costly for example in the context of a DHT where an additional lookup must be performed to fetch the pubkey.\r\n\r\ncc @zscole who apparently did some libp2p benchmarking using RSA",
