    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Within our tests, we actually used [ed25519 for peer identity](https://github.com/whiteblock/p2p-tests/blob/master/client/main.go#L108). Although we're only just beginning to touch the surface of our research and testing efforts, based on our initial findings, it appears to have resulted in a significant amount of overhead, but we weren't specifically evaluating this implementation, so I don't have enough data to provide anything conclusive at this time. Either way, ed25519 should technically be faster and more secure than RSA. \r\n\r\nThis is something we can easily target and benchmark in future test series though. I'm currently working on designing the next test phase, so I'll keep this in mind and design a test case around it if the results would be of value. If anyone has any suggestions or ideas as to the specifics of what we should focus on, please feel free to share. You can also open an issue in our [p2p test repo](https://github.com/whiteblock/p2p-tests).",
